arts.ttl: Austria secure record win as they humiliate San Marino 10-0
arts.sum:
Austria recorded the biggest win in their history as they thrashed minnows San Marino 10-0 in Vienna.

The 9-0 victory over Malta in April 1977 previously stood as Austria's biggest ever victory, but Ralf Rangnick's men have broken that record after trouncing San Marino in a World Cup qualifier.
